e-mail: promed@usa.healthnet.org
[Mr. Porter blames the warming oceans, but the cycle may be more complex.
The warming oceans kill the algae that live on the coral, resulting in
coral death. Water that was filtered by the coral and its algae are no
longer doing that job and we are seeing the results with an increase of
human pathogens in the water. It is only my theory. If some one has more
scientific evidence on the relationship between corals and human disease,
please share it with us. - Mod.TG
